<p>The <b>Dosa or Dosai</b> is a popular south Indian dish. Dosa is made from <a href="/wiki/Rice" title="Rice">rice</a> and <a href="/wiki/Urad_(bean)" title="Urad (bean)">black lentils</a>. It is a typical South Indian food, eaten for breakfast or dinner, and is rich in <a href="/wiki/Carbohydrate" title="Carbohydrate">carbohydrates</a> and <a href="/wiki/Protein" title="Protein">protein</a>.</p>
